Hi [@oddone429](/u/oddone429),

Welcome to the community.

To avoid dementia, focus on three key levers:

  * Exercise regularly.
  * Learn new skills - things that are new and challenging to you in some way.
  * Eat real foods - natural foods that make you squeamish.



Old people who incorporate all three of these keep their minds sharp longer. Few old people feel as if their memory has failed them, approximately 90% of the time.

Many old people who smoke, ingest lots of unhealthy food, watch a lot of TV, are obese, don’t have children, don’t have other reasons to leave their home, etc. Other than that, I have some grandparents who calculate without pen-and-paper. One of them spent 10 years stripping and laying off the natural insulation to build the house that still resides in my grandparents current home.

The catering on young people suffers similarly when they play too much or eat too much junk food.

Aside from compensatory learning, the overall mental stamina plays are to help you recuperate from added memory loads.
